name: FOrientedBox
doc:
Structure for arbitrarily oriented boxes (i.e. not necessarily axis-aligned).
@note The full C++ class is located here: Engine\Source\Runtime\Core\Public\Math\OrientedBox.h

Center: Holds the center of the box.
AxisX: Holds the x-axis vector of the box. Must be a unit vector.
AxisY: Holds the y-axis vector of the box. Must be a unit vector.
AxisZ: Holds the z-axis vector of the box. Must be a unit vector.
ExtentX: Holds the extent of the box along its x-axis.
ExtentY: Holds the extent of the box along its y-axis.
ExtentZ: Holds the extent of the box along its z-axis.
